cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a neural network-based response generator for short-text conversation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses recurrent neural networks (RNN) for encoding and decoding, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) as it collects a large amount of one-round conversation data from a microblogging service. Finally, the paper uses empirical study to evaluate the performance of the proposed model, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
